@node "Reqs" "Requirements"

  @{b}@{u}What you need to be able to run Annotate 3@{uu}@{ub}

   AmigaOS 4.0 or higher and ReAction.
   AmigaOS 3.0 or higher (possibly even OS2.04) and MUI.
   MorphOS 1.0 or higher and MUI.
   AROS with Zune.

@endnode
@node "History" "History"

  @{fg shine}@{b}What's new and what Annotate already features!
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}* NEW *@{fg text} Tool commands now get a console output window if they output anything.

   @{fg fill}* NEW *@{fg text} Made the "Quit with changes" requester much better and allows to save.

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Spell corrected guide by Tom Breeden. Thank you!

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Fixed string escaping in the XML prefs such that any characters in paths
           etc can be saved without causing XML parse errors.

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Fixed the Tools edit page which was completely screwed on the MUI versions.

   @{fg fill}* NEW *@{fg text} Added Alt as qualifier to temporarely switch selection mode between normal
           and rectangular mode.

   @{fg fill}* NEW *@{fg text} Improved rectangular selection such that the width is not dependent on the
           length of the last line the mouse is over.

   @{fg fill}* NEW *@{fg text} Updated the behavior of upper/lower case when there is no selection.
           Now it changes the character under the cursor and advances by char ahead.

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Fixed the $ VER : string which appeared empty in some versions.

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Optimized the text redrawing when selecting text and in other situations.

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} * FIX * Fixed crash when iconifying and reopening.


  @{fg shine}@{b}v3.0
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   ** Completely rewrote Ed Exchange so it can now be used along-side the editor
      windows as a quicklist of editors.
   
   ** Added the setting to have a scrollbar on the right side.
   
   ** Implemented different mark modes: Ann, Notepad, Quick where NotePad makes
      Annotate's selection of text behave like "normal" text editors.
   
   ** Annotate can now open on a custom screen with a chosen backdrop image,
      frontmost public screen.
   
   ** Added find/replace history so you can use up/down arrow keys to navigate
      old searches.

   * Added a setting to set the filename in the window titlebar.
   
   * Implemented marking of edited lines in the scrollbar.
   
   * Made it possible to add external syntax files.
   
   * Monitors file changes, and alerts when a file was changed on disk.
   
   * Added "Hide and Open New" to the menu.
   
   * Added a frame for the status bar so no strange colors have to be used.
   
   * Added an 'All' button to the Replace prompt.
   
   * Selecting Clear selection now clears the selection in all windows if
     UNIX copy'n'paste is used..
   
   * Match brace now finds unmatching brace combinations like ( [ ) ].
   
   * Added a switch to disable horiz scrolling with the vertical mouse wheel
     when the mouse is outside the window.
   
   * Showing the color for each color setting in a box.
   
   * Added the tools settings to the prefs.
   
   * Made optimizations in when and how often the editor should be redrawn.
   
   * Added arexx commands SHOW_EX_EDITOR and HIDE_EDITOR.
   
   * Fixed pasting of 8-bit characters for OS3.
   
   * Added setting to put filename in window title.

   * Fixed saving of projects which didn't work very well.
   
   * Save when window becomes inactive now also applies when hiding.
   
   * Made it scroll to the correct last line also when a file is loaded hidden.
   
   * Fixed loading of macros.
   
   * RAmiga+w now behaves exactly as double-clicking some word or symbol.
   
   * Fixed replace which always forgot the first line.
   
   * Make it possible to replace equal, but case-different, strings when
     non-case is selected.
   
   * Fixed starting to find at the very end or beginning.
   
   * Cleaned up the source code a lot by renamed a lot of functions to make it
     more coherent.
   
   * Fixed gfx garbage when scrolling.
   
   * Fixed complex syntax type with endtoken parsing.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.7
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Annotate can now be compiled for MUI instead of ReAction!
      The OS4 version uses ReAction since it looks better and has more
      features under OS4. All other targets are compiled for MUI but
      can be compiled for ReAction/ClassAct as well.

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} AROS is now supported.

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Added simple project support. This makes it possible to save and
      load a project file which will contain the current configuration of
      opened files and their editors/windows. Makes for a quick way of
      reopening all the files and windows you were working on yesterday,
      or before a crash.

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Annotate's editors are now AppWindows which means that you can drop
      icons on them to open files.

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Having a requester opening when Ann is started from Workbench is
      now optional.

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Realtime update of colors in the editor when they are changed from
      the Config.

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Added an expiration date to the "remembered lines".

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Fixed the auto-update function so that it will download the correct
      binary for your OS. (Will of course only work the next time.)

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Pasting an text that started with a linefeed at the end of a line
      didn't work correctly.

   @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Possibly fixed some random garbage that could have been inserted
      when cut'n'pasting vertical blocks with empty lines in the middle.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.6.4
  ~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Ported to AmigaOS 3.x and MorphOS!
     It works with the latest ClassAct that can be found on Aminet, but
     it works better with ReAction from AmigaOS 3.5+. Note that on MorphOS
     the latest window.class looks for the wrong version of icon.library
     and fails to open completely. Use an older window.class in this case.
     This will be improved in the future.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a Find next change/Find previous change function to the Search menu.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a weirdness when checking for new updates and none were available
     but extra files were available.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Made errors more clear when shown in the status line.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed copying of  a line to the find or replace field with a vertical
     selection.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.6.3
  ~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Made edited lines appear with a different background color.
     The color is selected by the user.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a new way of finding and replacing words by matching
     only whole unbroken words.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added PortablE as a language with syntax highlighting.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} New icons composed by David Braconnier. Thanks! :)

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} When reopening the same file twice and selected to bring the already
     open editor to front, the current editor was cleared.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The uppercase/lowercase function didn't work on a vertical block selection.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed Ctrl+MMB moving of a vertical selection.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added "mandatory" to the qualifying And/OrTokens to force matching
     this qualification for a particular language at all times.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now tries to not clear a selection when undoing something.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed random insertion of null bytes when loading an MS-DOS file with CR+LF.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Better handling of multiline tokens like for example /* C/C++ comments */.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Better handling of files with very long lines, such as if one accidently
     loads a binary file.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.6.2
  ~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Starts quicker because it doesn't open all gadget classes until they are needed.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a bug in the auto update code.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a crash if expat.library was not found.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added an option to disable the use of system beep/flash.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a few bugs regarding vertical selection/block copy'n'paste and undo/redo.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Changed the scroll wheel acceleration for the scrollbar so that it will
      never jumps more than one page at a time.


  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.6.1
  ~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Using expat.library instead of linking with expat.lib. Saves 150kB.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Improved archive bit handling.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added HTML as a syntax highlighting.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added LaTeX as a syntax highlighting.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added the attribute "caseinsensitive"/"ignorecase" to make it easy to
          implement syntax for case insensitive languages, such as HTML.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added function to let paste replace a selection.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a kind of UNIX primary selection way of copy'n'paste using the
          middle mouse button. When it is enabled it is possible to select text
          in any editor and then by a click on the MMB paste this text in any
          opened editor without activating its window first!
          Holding Ctrl while clicking the MMB will move the text.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now Ann asks if you try to open the same file twice.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now Ann asks if you try to overwrite a file that exists when using Save as.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added "Wrap selected or all text" to the Tools menu to make it possible
          to wrap a text that is already loaded.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Holding the Ctrl key while closing a window makes it discard all changes
          to the file without asking.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added an iconify gadget which at the moment closes a window and places
          the editor in the hidden editors list in Ed Exchange.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed an error regarding undo when more than one file was selected to be
          opened. This error could result in a number of different behaviours.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Sometimes there was garbage displayed when syntax highlighting was enabled.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} If moving the editor window while replacing interactively answered Yes
          to the requester.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Arexx command GET WIN NAME without a number caused a crash.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} When making your own syntax file Ann could crash if there was an
          error with the OrTokens tag.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now the double-click to select word accepts 8-bit characters so that
          non-English words can be completely selected.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a few bugs regarding the Exchange Ed. This needs a total rewrite though.


  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.6
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} (Major since v2.5) Syntax highlighting with current support for
           C/C++, Amiga-E, AmigaGuide and XML.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} (Major since v2.5) Unlimited Undo/Redo!

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} (Major since v2.5) Ann can remember where in a file you last edited
           and scroll there when the file is opened.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} (Major since v2.5) Double/triple-click to select word, syntactic
           phrase, line or bracket contents.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed many (hopefully all) Undo/Redo bugs, some of which were nasty.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Reimplemented wildcard find. It is now possible to enter a DOS pattern
           string to search for. It will match an entire line.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Multiple cursors when using "Last saved" to revert a file.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It was impossible to select text on the first line.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a subtle problem with match brace causing it to mismatch sometimes.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Improved the smart window placement.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a small ARexx bug regarding cursor placement.


  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.5.3 (AutoUpdate)
  ~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Finally Ann is on the same level as other modern editors:
      It has got Undo/Redo!
      Beware of possible bugs. May not work will all kinds of editing,
      like vert selections.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added the option "Delete key deletes selection".

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It is is now possible to double-click to select a word, line, or the
      contents between ({[brackets and braces]}).

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Ann can now remember which line you last visited in a file when
      you save it so the next time you load it, Ann will scroll there
      automatically.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added functionality to allow the Tab key to perform indentation instead
      of inserting tab characters or spaces.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Made it possible to do circular finds. When no more matches are found
      it will start over from the top.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now the line in the middle of the window will be seen in the status field
      when scrolling with the scroll bar to make it a lot easier to find a
      particular line.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Ann respects file protection bits.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Ann can now automatically switch tab-key and indentation mode depending
      on if the file loaded contains tab characters or not.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added "Clear Selection" as a menu option to provide a simple way of
      clearing a selection from the keyboard. Default hotkey is 'RAmiga +'.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a couple of minor bug regarding syntax highlighting, including
      some update of the AnnotateSyntax.xml file.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Many more small changes and enhancements.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.5.2 (AutoUpdate)
  ~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a small error detected by OS4 Final when entering the config
      on OS4 Final.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed another error of the same kind related to the configurable
      part of the Tools menu in Ann.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The Auto Update feature was broken and does not work correctly in
      v2.5.1. It works in v2.5 and v2.5.2 though.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The correct page was not remembered when reentering Config.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.5.1 (AutoUpdate)
  ~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Finally we have Syntax Highlighting! Currently there is support for
      the following languages: C/C++, Amiga-E, Amiga Guide, XML.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Changing of font size was not recognized unless the font was also changed.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Tab-settings and Auto-indent are individual for each editor now.
      Use the Apply button in the Config to set it for all opened editors.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Match Brace has been fixed and enhanced a bit.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Window left and top edge could not be 0.


  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.5
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Saving config only saved to ENVARC: which made it appear
     as if settings weren't saved until you rebooted.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added Auto Update which means that Ann now is able to update
     itself over Internet. It will by default check for updates every
     five days or less.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Ann is now a true OS4 Application, meaning that it has full
     Application.library support. Unfortunately there is no
     application handler out there right now.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added Search from beginning and Search backwards for Find
     and Replace.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added Find Previous to the menu.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The Find requester outputted some debug.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now Esc works in the Find and Replace requesters.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a few arexx command;
     ACTION REPLACE - Replace without opening the replace requester.
     ACTION FIND - Find next and return a bool.
     ACTION FIND_IN_LINE - Find only on current line and return bool.
     INSERT TAB - Insert tab characters.
     BACKSPACE - As hitting backspace.
     SET SEARCH_FROM_BEG - Set this flag for Find and Replace.
     SET SEARCH_BACKWARDS - Set this flag for Find and Replace.
     HELP - Write a list of all commands to a file.

     Included an AmigaE to C translation rexx script that demonstrates the
     potential of scripting with Annotate. It also does a pretty good job
     of doing the dirty work when porting E to C :)

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Doesn't jump to the beginning of the file when
     reverting to last saved.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed loading of files as parameters, both shift-clicked
     from WB and supplied via CLI.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Text selection is visible while selecting.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Holding Ctrl while copying text with MMB cuts text.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added possibility to paste with MMB click a la UNIX.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added Cycle Editor in menu on key LAlt+Tab to easily swap
     between editor windows.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Reading and writing hotkeys didn't work correctly.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} A couple of other fixes regarding the editing of hotkeys,
     such as they not working with CapsLock on, and letting repeat
     through as regular keys.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} CursorX doesn't jump to AutoX after Find but stays intuitively
     where is it.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added confirmation requester for all unsaved editors when
     quitting. The requester also now contains the filename.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added the option to keep only one instance of Ann running
     even when starting another copy.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed possible crash in the Ed Exchange editor.


  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.4
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Closing the Config without a font selected (which is default)
     caused a crash. Fixed. (sorry about that... :-( )
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} All hotkeys (pretty much) are now editable!!
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Scroll-wheel support - context sensitive! Scroll over the text
     and it scrolls "Scroll Unit" lines at a time, scroll over the
     scroll bar and it scrolls pages, scroll to the right of the
     text and it scrolls horizontally.
     Also the horizontal wheel (should) work.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now finally full tab-key support with tab-stops and all!
     Placing the mouse on a line with tabs, moving the cursor with the
     arrow keys, wordwrap, it should all work as expected now.
     Only vertical column selections doesn't work well with tabs now
     (they really can't either as they may cut a tab in half which
     would be illegal).
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added Tabs to Spaces and Spaces to Tabs functions.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The default path can now be explicitly selected in the config.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a new marker in the scroll bar that shows the last place
     you were with the cursor if you scroll away and place the cursor
     somewhere else using the mouse. Very practical and makes it dead
     easy to find your way back to where you were.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added option to autosave every X minutes. Autosave only writes
     the backup file if it didn't previously existed, if backups is
     is switched on. This prevents accidental overwrite of an old
     file that you may have opened to create a new file from.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added option to autosave when the edit window gets inactive.
     Very practical if you switch between Ann and for example a
     compiler in a shell, you then don't have to save your changes
     manually, just click outside Ann's window, e.g. in the shell
     and it will automatically save.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a function to switch off the "cursor memory" which may seem
     a bit annoying for those not used to Ann. This means you need to
     switch off "Remember cursor positions" to remove the cursor memory.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a few new short commands:
     Ctrl+Left mouse  immediately starts a selection as a non-sticky
     selection editor would do.
     Middle mouse  immediately selects and copys a text without moving
     the cursor or cancelling another selection. Using Shift copies the
     text into clip unit 1 instead of 0 which is default.
     These, and the other mouse-"keys" are not editable.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It is now possible to open many files at the same time from the
     file-requester.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added switch top make the cursor follow when scrolling using the
     numpad scroll-keys.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added key to get cursor into view. It defaults to numpad-0.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added switch to make new windows open relative to parent window
     instead of the default position.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Forgot to check the "Smart window placing" switch. It was always
     used.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now compiled with NewLib which made the exe 50kB smaller than
     with CLib2. Unfortunately all new features added another 100kB.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Ann shouldn't die the Linux death when given Ctrl-C anymore.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} A lot of other minor fixes, like the save requester gave no
     busy-pointer to the editor, replacing repetitive characters
     didn't work, save close now quits if the last editor was closed,
     Shrink/Enlarge Ann works now.


  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.3
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} ReAction is now used for just about everything except for the editor
     itself! The Config, most notable, has been completely remade and now
     has the same structure as SYS:Prefs/GUI. The remake of the config
     also made it easier to add a lot more settings.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Tab characters are now supported! It's not 100% perfect but way
     better than nothing.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} UTF-8 support! It is possible to load files with UTF-8 to Latin1
     conversion, and to paste text with UTF-8 to Latin1 conversion.
     I don't know how to convert anything else than Latin1 now though.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Word wrap can now be performed when loading a text file.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added busy-pointer to the editor windows when a requester is open.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a bunch of sneaky hotkeys that could be very useful:
     * Ctrl+Del  deletes everything to the right of the cursor.
     * Ctrl+BackSpace  deletes everything to the left of the cursor.
     * Shift+Del  deletes all white spaces to the right of the cursor.
     * Shift+BackSpace  deletes all white spaces to the left of the cursor.
     * Ctrl+Enter  causes the very unique Anti-Enter! This is a
       linefeed upwards in the text! (See the guide for more info.)
     * Shift+Enter  temporarily inverts the Auto Indent flag.
     * Alt+BackSpace  deletes a "tabs size" number of characters to the left.
     * See the guide for a complete list of old and new key combinations.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a lot of hotkeys that didn't work.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It is now possible to change font.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added proper Use and Last Saved to the Config.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It is now possible to side-shift text in steps of tab size, not
     just one space at a time.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It is also possible to side-shift one line of text without
     selecting it first.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Changed backup behaviour to rename the old file as #?.bak instead
     of just writing two copies when saving.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The status line now has its own background colour and it is fixed
     to the bottom of the window instead of the bottom of the text.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Enter now responds to key-repeat.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Arrow-keys now have the option to run through lines instead of
     stopping at the beginning or end of the line it is on.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now it is possible to abort a replace operation or a repeating
     macro event by hitting Escape or clicking the window close button.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added some info, like "Replace - Done" and "Replace - Text not found"
     when replacing.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It is now possible to have newly paste text selected.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Various small cosmetic enhancements.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed the scroll bar which got inverted when the window was very
     small and there were only few lines of text.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed pasting of multiple clip chunks, such as from YAM which often
     caused garbage to be pasted into Ann. Now with UTF-8 paste support
     it is very nice to be able to paste UTF-8 e-mails into Ann to be
     able to read them comfortably :-)

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a couple of bugs regarding selection of text. If in column
     select mode and side-shifting until the block shrunk to zero size
     it would crash. There were other old crashy selection bugs as well
     that are fixed.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a couple of cosmetic selection bugs.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The text and background color wasn't used properly.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed "Repeat next event" which didn't work at all as it got eaten
     by mouse move events.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.2
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} When saving prefs the XML prefs file did not become well-formed and
     could therefore not be read. How stupid of me to not test that in
     the final release (it obviously worked in my betas).

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Colors (pens) for most things can now be edited.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} New look scroll bar! No more black boring rectangle (unless you
     want to of course).

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Diminished the "WINDOW TO SMALL TO SCROLL!!!" message even further.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now Ann preserves protection bits of files which makes it a lot
     more convenient to edit scripts with the 's' bit set for example.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can choose to work with a filled cursor contrary to the
     unfilled box.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added Apply and Cancel to the preferences.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now the Find and Number requesters only require Enter in the
     string/integer gadget to close.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} When the mouse is pressed down to scroll or mark text and another
     program pops up a requester, the mouse won't stick to Ann any more.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now the CPU-loop is all gone which means no flickering when the
     mouse is pressed down somewhere in the editor or scroller.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a few small cosmetic issues.

  @{fg shine}@{b}v2.1
  ~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now it's possible to have text unselected after it has been copied.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Annotate handles Carriage Return (from PC texts) while reading and
     a setting specifies if you want to save with or without Carriage
     Return unrelative to the input file.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Go to the beginning of the line now has one additional meaning:
     Shift+Left or Home can now optionally place the cursor at the first
     character in a line instead of at the very beginning.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Annotate can now place successive windows in a smart way, cascading
     I think, so they are easier to manage.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} If you never use Arexx with Annotate you can switch it off. This
     will effectively remove the "Could not create arexx port" message
     that always popped up if multiple instances of Annotate was started.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The autoscroll when clicking in any outer region of the text in the
     window can now be slightly delayed to make it possible to put the
     cursor on a character in this area without accidently scrolling away.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added the current filename to the screen title bar to make it easier
     to see what file is being edited if the name doesn't fit in the
     status line.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now Annotate won't use 100% CPU when holding down the mouse button.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Several code speed-ups when loading and saving files.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Enabled pasting of 8-bit ASCII, and tab.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It is now possible to have the Tab key insert real tabs into the text.
     (It will only be displayed as one unprintable (blank) character though,
     and will not induce an indentation as may be expected. A rewrite of
     the draw routines will have to be made for that to work.)

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} PC-keys PgUp, PgDown, Home, End works as intended now.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Annotate now remembers paths and filenames in requesters all the time
     and everywhere. Also saves path so one can have a default path.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Made it possible to resize the window with contents.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a status message "Not found" after searching when nothing was found.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The "WINDOW TO SMALL TO SCROLL!!!" message can now be diminished
     by letting Annotate scale the Scroll Unit to the window size.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now the editor window can be placed where one wants it and then
     press "Get Window Dimensions" instead of guessing and entering the
     values manually.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now using XML for prefs saving and loading, removed s:AnnConfig saving.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Removed the little window that popped up in the top-left corner at startup.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Changed some menu hotkeys so they will work on (Swedish) PC-keyboards.
     In the future all hotkeys will be configurable.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed the ever varying text mark color when used on hi/true-colour
     screens.

   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Set the WFLG_NewLookMenus flag to make the menus look up-to-date.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a checkmark to the Line/Vert select menu item to make it
     easier to see what mode one is in.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed paste from empty clipboard which switched off Auto indent.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed paste from empty clipboard which marked the file as modified.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Status wasn't displayed as modified when deleting characters, now it is.

@endnode
