@node "SET" 
Subcommands of SET with their params and return values:

WIN_STATS      Moves and resizes the current window.

     call      SET WIN_STATS WindowX WindowY Width Height
     
     params    WindowX,WindowY,Width,Height are all numbers describing 
               where to move and how to size the current window.
               
     result    "WindowX WindowY Width Height" which are all numbers 
               describing the resulting window size and position.
               
               
DEF_WIN_STATS  Sets default window size and position for new windows.

     call      SET DEF_WIN_STATS WindowX WindowY Width Height
     
     params    WindowX,WindowY,Width,Height are numbers used as the new 
               default window (see Config requester).
               
     result    "WindowX WindowY Width Height" which are all numbers 
               describing the resulting default window size and position.


WRK_WIN

     call      WRK_WIN WindowName
     
     params    WindowName is a the currently loaded filename of the window
               you want all further rexx commands to be directed towards.

     result    WindowName if the window WindowName was found.


GRAPHIC_UPDATE

     call      SET GRAPHIC_UPDATE ON/OFF
     
     params    ON or OFF. If you turn GRAPHIC_UPDATE off all rendering in 
               Ann will be stopped making most operations speed up. 
               Turning it back on will cause a total refresh.
               
     result    The status of GRAPHIC_UPDATE, namely ON or OFF.


SHOW_REQUEST

     call      SET SHOW_REQUEST ON/OFF
     
     params    ON or OFF. If you turn SHOW_REQUEST off all requester in 
               Ann will automatically return as if the OK gadget was 
               selected without even showing the requester to the user.
               
     result    The status of SHOW_REQUEST, namely ON or OFF.


FIND_TYPE      Used to set the Search Type gadget in the search requesters.

     call      SET FIND_TYPE TypeNum
     
     params    TypeNum is a number from 0 to 2 which mean:
               0 Case Sensitive
               1 Non-Case Sensitive
               2 Wild Cards
               
     result    The old FIND_TYPE TypeNum.


REPLACE_PROMPT_TYPE Used to set the Prompt Type gadget in the search requesters.

     call      SET REPLACE_PROMPT_TYPE TypeNum
     
     params    TypeNum is a number from 0 to 2 which mean:
               0 No Prompt
               1 Prompt Once
               2 Always Prompt

     result    The old REPLACE_PROMPT_TYPE TypeNum.


FIND_TEXT      Used to set the Find string gadget in the search requesters.

     call      SET FIND_TEXT String
     
     params    String is a string that you want in the string gadget.
               
     result    The old FIND_TEXT String.


REPLACE_TEXT   Used to set the Replace string gadget in the search requesters.

     call      SET REPLACE_TEXT String
     
     params    String is a string that you want in the string gadget.
               
     result    The old REPLACE_TEXT String.


STATUS_LINE    Used to set the current windows status line.

     call      SET STATUS_LINE String
     
     params    String is a string that you want written into the current windows 
               status line.
               
     result    none.


DRAWER         Used to set the Drawer string gadget in the file requester.

     call      SET DRAWER String
     
     params    String is a string that you want in the string gadget.
               
     result    The old DRAWER String.


PATTERN        Used to set the Pattern string gadget in the file requester.

     call      SET PATTERN String
     
     params    String is a string that you want in the string gadget.
               
     result    The old PATTERN String.


SEEK_LINE      Used to set the LineNum gadget in the seek LineNum requester.

     call      SET SEEK_LINE Num
     
     params    Num is a num that you want in the num gadget.
               
     result    The old SEEK_LINE num.


ASCII_CODE     Used to set the Ascii code gadget in the insert ascii code requester.

     call      SET ASCII_CODE Num
     
     params    Num is a num that you want in the num gadget.
               
     result    The old ASCII_CODE num.


SEARCH_FROM_BEG  Used to set the Ascii code gadget in the insert ascii code requester.

     call      SET SEARCH_FROM_BEG ON/OFF
     
     params    Bool where "ON" mean true and everything else means false.
               
     result    The state. This will be reset to OFF after each call to
               ACTION REPLACE, ACTION FIND or DOMENU FIND_NEXT.


SEARCH_BACKWARDS  Used to set the Ascii code gadget in the insert ascii code requester.

     call      SET SEARCH_BACKWARDS ON/OFF
     
     params    Bool where "ON" mean true and everything else means false.
               
     result    The state.


@endnode
@node "GET" 
Subcommands of GET with their params and return values:

SCR_SIZE       Used to get the size of the screen.

     call      GET SCR_SIZE
     
     result    "Width Height" of the screen Ann is running on.


WIN_STATS      Used to get the current window size and position.

     call      GET WIN_STATS
     
     result    "WindowX WindowY Width Height" which are all numbers 
               describing the current windows size and position.


DEF_WIN_STATS  Used to get the default window size and position.

     call      GET DEF_WIN_STATS
     
     result    "WindowX WindowY Width Height" which are all numbers 
               describing the default window size and position.


SEL_TEXT       Used to get the current selection.

     call      GET SEL_TEXT
     
     result    A string containing the current selection or an err if there 
               is no selection.


CHR            Used to get the character under the cursor

     call      GET CHR
     
     result    "char ascii CursorX CursorY" where char is the character 
               under the cursor, ascii is the ascii value of char and 
               CursorX and CursorY is the position of the cursor.


WIN_NAME       Used to get the name of a window

     call      GET WIN_NAME WindowNum

     params    WindowNum is a number of the window you want the name of or 
               it can be 0 if you want the name of the current window.

     result    A string contaning the window name or an err if the 
               WindowNum is higher then the number of windows open.


FILENAME       Used to get the filename for the current editor window.
               Same as GET WIN_NAME 0.

     call      GET FILENAME

     result    A string containing the window name or an err if there
               is no open window.


SEL_SIZE       Used to get the start and end points of the selection

     call      GET SEL_SIZE
     
     result    "MarkStartX MarkStartY MarkEndX MarkEndY" which are all 
               numbers describing the cursor positions of the selection 
               start and end. If there is no selection an err will be 
               returned.


EX_ED_NAME     Used to get the name of a external editor

     call      GET EX_ED_NAME EdNum
     
     params    EdNum is a number of the editor you want the name of.
               
     result    A string contaning the editor name or an err if the 
               EdNum is higher then the number of External editors open.


@endnode
@node "INSERT" 
Subcommands of INSERT with their params and return values:

STRING         Used to insert a string of text at the cursor position.

     call      INSERT STRING String
     
     params    String is the string you want inserted.
               
     result    "TRUE" if all went well.


RETURN         Used to insert LFs at the cursor position.

     call      INSERT RETURN Num
     
     params    Num is the number of returns to insert.
               
     result    "TRUE" if all went well.


SPACE          Used to insert spaces at the cursor position.

     call      INSERT SPACE Num
     
     params    Num is the number of spaces to insert.
               
     result    "TRUE" if all went well.


TAB            Used to insert tabs at the cursor position.

     call      INSERT TAB Num

     params    Num is the number of tabs to insert.

     result    "TRUE" if all went well.

@endnode
@node "MOVE_CURSOR" 
Subcommands of MOVE_CURSOR with their params and return values:

REL            Used to move the cursor some distance form where it is.

     call      MOVE_CURSOR REL DeltaX DeltaY
     
     params    DeltaX and DeltaY are numbers which are used as offsets to 
               move the cursor from it's current position.
               
     result    "DeltaX DeltaY X Y" where DeltaX and DeltaY are the actual 
               distance the cursor was able to move and X and Y are the 
               cursors new absolute position.


ABS            Used to move the cursor to an absolute position.

     call      MOVE_CURSOR ABS X Y
     
     params    X and Y are numbers which are used as absolute positions to 
               move the cursor to.
               
     result    "DeltaX DeltaY X Y" where DeltaX and DeltaY is the distance 
               the cursor moved and X and Y are the actual new cursors
               absolute position.

@endnode
@node "ACTION" 
Subcommands of ACTION with their params and return values:

ACTION REPLACE Start replacing without opening the replace requester.

     call      ACTION REPLACE
     
     params    None.
               
     result    The FIND_TEXT replaced by REPLACE_TEXT in all occurrences
               from the cursor or beginning, to the end or beginning
               depending on settings of SEARCH_FROM_BEG and
               SEARCH_BACKWARDS.


ACTION FIND - Find next that returns a bool.

     call      ACTION FIND
     
     params    None.
               
     result    A bool (5=true, 0=false) indicating if the FIND_TEXT was
               found. It will start searching from the cursor or beginning,
               to the end or beginning depending on settings of SEARCH_FROM_BEG
               and SEARCH_BACKWARDS.


ACTION FIND_IN_LINE - Find only on current line and returns bool.

     call      ACTION FIND_IN_LINE String
     
     params    String to be found on the current line only.
               
     result    A bool (5=true, 0=false) indicating if the String was
               found on the current line to the right of the cursor.

@endnode
@node "REQUESTER" 
Subcommands of REQUESTER with their params and return values:

ANSWER         Offers the user one of three choices.

     call      REQUESTER ANSWER Text Cancel OK Maybe
     
     params    Text is a string and the question being asked.
               Maybe, Cancel and OK are strings for up to three gadgets (
               you don't have to use them all).
               
     result    A string which contains the option chosen.


LIST           Offers the user one of many choices and a cancel.

     call      REQUESTER LIST WindowTitle CancelText Option1 Optoin2 ...
     
     params    WindowTitle is the window title and should be the question 
               begin asked.
               CancelText is a string for the Cancel gadgets text.
               Option1 ... are the option of the list.
               
     result    A string which contains the option chosen. This option 
               could be any of the Option texts or the Cancel text.

NUM            Lets the user input a number.

     call      REQUESTER NUM WindowTitle NumGadText DefaultNum
     
     params    WindowTitle is the text put into the window title.
               NumGadText is the text put beside the num gadget.
               DefaultNum is the number the requester comes up with.
               
               
     result    The number the user selected or an err if they canceled.


STRING         Lets the user input a number.

     call      REQUESTER STRING WindowTitle StringGadText OKGad CancelGad
     
     params    WindowTitle is the text put into the window title.
               StringGadText is the text put beside the string gadget.
               OKGad is the text used for the OK gadget.
               CancelGad is the text used for the Cancel gadget.
               
     result    The string the user input or an err if they canceled.

@endnode
@node "Other_Commands" "Other Commands"
ANN_VERSION    To find out what version of Ann you're talking to.

     call      ANN_VERSION
               
     result    A string containing Annotates version.

DEL            Deletes characters from the cursor position.

     call      DEL Num
          
     params    Num is the number of characters to delete.
               
     result    "TRUE" if all went well.


BACKSPACE      Deletes characters from to the left of the cursor, and moves the cursor.

     call      BACKSPACE Num

     params    Num is the number of characters to delete.

     result    "TRUE" if all went well.


OPEN_IN_WIN    Loads a file into the current window

     call      OPEN_IN_WIN FileName
          
     params    FileName is a string with the name of the file to be loaded
               
     result    none.


OPEN_EX_EDITOR Loads a file into the current window and puts the editor in 
               the current window into the external editor list.

     call      OPEN_EX_EDITOR FileName
          
     params    FileName is a string with the name of the file to be loaded
               
     result    none.


OPEN_WIN       Opens a window and puts the first editor in the external 
               editor list into it.

     call      OPEN_WIN
     
     result    none.


SHOW_EX_EDITOR Opens a window for any hidden (external) editor by referring
               to it by the filename of the already opened but hidden editor.
               It will first match the complete path but if it cannot be found
               it will try again matching only the filename. Case insensitive.

     call      SHOW_EX_EDITOR FileName

     result    RC=0 for success, 5 for failure.


HIDE_EDITOR    Hides the window for any open editor by referring to it by the
               filename.
               It will first match the complete path but if it cannot be found
               it will try again matching only the filename. Case insensitive.

     call      HIDE_EDITOR FileName

     result    RC=0 for success, 5 for failure.


CLOSE_BOTH     Closes the current window and the editor in it. Same a 
               clicking the close gadget on the window.

     call      CLOSE_BOTH
     
     result    none.


CLOSE_WIN      Closes the current window and puts its editor into the 
               external editor list.

     call      CLOSE_WIN
     
     result    none.


CLOSE_ED       Closes the editor in the current window and puts its puts 
               the first editor from the external editor list into it.

     call      CLOSE_ED
     
     result    none.


EXCHANGE_EDS   Exchanges an external editor with the editor in the current 
               window.

     call      EXCHANGE_EDS Num
          
     params    Num is the number of the external editor.
               
     result    none if the Num was valid else an err is returned.


HELP           Get a complete list of all arexx commands supported by Ann.

     call      HELP Filename
          
     params    Filename is a place to write the list of commands.
               
     result    The result of the operation. 10 (ERROR) if it failed.

